[Claude]: Now I have a clear picture of the SupportBundleService validation. Let me analyze the critical issue:

The `ensureFileWithinBundleDir` method uses:
```java
bundleDir.resolve(filename).toFile().getCanonicalPath().startsWith(bundleDir.toFile().getCanonicalPath())
```

This uses `String.startsWith()` on canonical paths. The key issue here is the **prefix collision** vulnerability: if `bundleDir` is `/data/graylog/support-bundle`, then `getCanonicalPath()` returns `/data/graylog/support-bundle` (no trailing slash). A filename like `../support-bundle-evil/secret.txt` would resolve to `/data/graylog/support-bundle-evil/secret.txt` after canonicalization, which starts with `/data/graylog/support-bundle` — this BYPASSES the check!

